The paper discusses the variability mechanisms offered by modeling languages, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). It also proposes a framework for managing language variabilities, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the UML, which is a modeling language used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
